  "number": 4087,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/4087",
  "title": "feat(routing): add a \"single index\" compatibility mode",
  "body": "This mode has as goal to flatten the URL structure to avoid the indexName of the root index in the URL when there's only one URL.\r\n\r\nUsage:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nimport { history } from 'instantsearch.js/lib/router';\r\nimport { singleIndex } from 'instantsearch.js/lib/stateMappings';\r\n\r\ninstantsearch({\r\n  // ...\r\n  indexName: \"blabla\",\r\n  routing: {\r\n    router: history(),\r\n    stateMapping: singleIndex(\"blabla\"),\r\n  },\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nRight now it's not yet possible to use this router in TS because InstantSearch itself isn't generic, and trying to make this happen was causing me a cascade of Generic issues. For now you need to cast it (`stateMapping: singleIndex(\"blabla\") as StateMapping<UiState>`).\r\n\r\nBREAKING CHANGE: Default URLs have changed, and now will contain the full state, which includes the index name. You can use the old behaviour by using the `singleIndex` stateMapping, and passing the index to synchronise in the argument.\r\n\r\nhttps://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/IFW-941\r\n",
